# Module Architecture Summary (Student OS - Stage 7.7)

This document provides a technical overview of the current system architecture, data structures, and feature states following the completion of Stage 7.

## 1. Local Storage Schema

All application data is consolidated in a single Local Storage key: `student_os_data`. The structure is partitioned into two primary "buckets": `courses` and `exams`.

### Courses Bucket (`store.courses[]`)
Each object in the `courses` array represents a persistent academic course, historically derived from a syllabus or manual entry.

```javascript
{
  "id": "course_1711134567890",      // Unique ID (prefixed with 'course_')
  "title": "Macroeconomics 2",       // Clean display name
  "moodleName": "מקרו כלכלה 2 (א)",   // Original source name (from Moodle)
  "nekaz": 4.5,                      // Credit points (null if TBD)
  "isConfigured": true,              // Flag: sum(gradeComponents.weight) === 100
  "lastSyllabusUpdate": "ISOString", // Date of last AI sync
  "staffMetadata": {
    "lecturer": "Dr. Cohen",
    "ta": "Yossi Levi"
  },
  "gradeComponents": [
    {
       "name": "Final Exam",
       "weight": 80,
       "score": 85,                  // User-entered (null if not yet graded)
       "isShield": false,
       "minPassGrade": 60 
    },
    { "name": "Midterm", "weight": 20, "score": 90, "isShield": true }
  ],
  "topics": ["GDP", "Inflation"],     // Raw topic strings
  "checklist": [                     // Checklist items derived from topics
    { "text": "GDP", "completed": false }
  ],
  "date": "TBD",                     // Legacy compatibility fields
  "time": "TBD"
}
```

### Exams Bucket (`store.exams[]`)
Each object in the `exams` array represents a specific exam session/instance.

```javascript
{
  "id": "exam_1711135567890",        // Unique ID (prefixed with 'exam_')
  "subject": "Macroeconomics 2",     // Matching core subject
  "date": "2026-06-15",
  "time": "09:00",
  "building": "Rabin",
  "room": "201",
  "type": "Moed A",                  // Moed A, B, C, or Final
  "isManual": true,                  // True if manually created by user
  "isShield": false
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Storage Sanitizer (Self-Healing)**: `storage.js` includes a persistent `_sanitize` method that automatically detects course-like objects (those with `gradeComponents` or `topics`) in the `exams` bucket and migrates them to `courses` on load.

