## 2. Syllabus UI & Integration State

The "Syllabus Harvester" is currently a cross-context feature spanning the Chrome Extension and the Web Dashboard.

### A. Extension Context (Moodle)
- **Injection**: A native "ייבא ל-Student OS" button is injected into Moodle course pages next to syllabus links (PDF/DOCX).
- **Extraction**: On click, it fetches the file, extracts text via `pdf.js`/`mammoth.js`, and sets a `pendingSyllabusImport` in shared extension storage.
- **Bridge**: Communicates via `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` to focus/create the Student OS tab.

### B. App Context (Dashboard & Insights Hub)
- **Handshake Receiver**: `app.js` listens for a `message` event. Once received, it triggers the Gemini AI agent to analyze the text.
- **Sync Alert**: Every successful import/update triggers a blocking `alert("Syllabus import process completed!");`.
- **Merge/Foundational Fuzzy Match**: 
  - **Current State**: The system automatically identifies existing courses based on bi-directional substring matching (`title.includes(agentName)` || `agentName.includes(title)`). If duplicates ("מקרו" vs "מקרו כלכלה") are found, it merges them and **deletes the redundant entries**.
  - **Aspiration**: We aspire to implement more advanced phonetic or Levenshtein-based matching in future stages to handle cross-language or complex typo scenarios.
- **Action Required UI**: 
  - **"Action Required" List**: A collapsible (details/summary) section in the Insights Hub showing courses missing Nekaz (Credits).
  - **Inline Editing**: Clicking the `Credits: [X]` badge on any course card opens a native `prompt` to directly update the Nekaz value without entering settings.

